Central retinal vein occlusion associated with clomiphene-induced ovulation.
OBJECTIVE: To report a case of central retinal vein occlusion associated with clomiphene citrate (CC).__0____ __DESIGN: Case study.__1____ __SETTING: Ophthalmology clinic of an academic hospital.__2____ __PATIENT(S): A 36-year-old woman referred from the infertility clinic for blurred vision.__3____ __INTERVENTION(S): Ophthalmic examination after CC therapy.__4____ __MAIN OUTCOME MEASURE(S): Central retinal vein occlusion after ovulation induction with CC.__5____ __RESULT(S): A 36-year-old Chinese woman developed central retinal vein occlusion after eight courses of CC.__6____ __A search of the literature on the thromboembolic complications of CC does not include this severe ophthalmic complication, although mild visual disturbance after CC intake is not uncommon.__7____ __CONCLUSION(S): This is the first reported case of central retinal vein occlusion after treatment with CC.__8____ __Extra caution is warranted in treating infertility patients with CC, and patients should be well informed of this side effect before commencement of therapy.
